You gotta sit Victoria down,

02:41.679 --> 02:43.178
tell her she can't come fishing with us.

02:43.180 --> 02:43.840
Victoria's going?

02:43.845 --> 02:45.548
- I thought girls weren't allowed.
- They aren't.

02:45.650 --> 02:47.016
Then why does she get to go?

02:47.018 --> 02:48.450
'Cause Carl invited her.

02:48.452 --> 02:49.618
Well, why didn't you invite me?

02:49.620 --> 02:50.919
'Cause I don't want you to go.

02:53.022 --> 02:54.223
Wow.

02:54.225 --> 02:55.591
No, no, nothing against you.

02:55.593 --> 02:56.625
I don't want her to go, either.

02:56.627 --> 02:57.793
It's gonna ruin the whole weekend.

02:57.795 --> 02:58.894
Well, then, don't go.

02:58.896 --> 03:00.329
It's my trip!

03:00.331 --> 03:03.065
Well, I mean, if it's your trip,

03:03.067 --> 03:05.367
then you can invite

03:05.369 --> 03:07.903
anybody you want to invite.

03:07.905 --> 03:09.571
No, no, no, no.

03:09.573 --> 03:10.772
I'm not playing this game.

03:10.774 --> 03:12.641
There's no game.

03:12.643 --> 03:14.509
I mean, if there was a game,

03:14.511 --> 03:16.411
I guess I'd be losing.

03:17.880 --> 03:19.314
Come on, don't be ridiculous.

03:19.316 --> 03:20.415
Am I ridiculous?

03:20.417 --> 03:22.351
Is that why you don't want to take me?

03:22.353 --> 03:23.518
No. I...

03:23.520 --> 03:24.386
I do. It's just, there's...

03:24.388 --> 03:25.854
Oh, yeah, bup. Don't.

03:25.856 --> 03:27.823
It's okay.

03:27.825 --> 03:28.724
Molly, don't be mad.

03:28.726 --> 03:30.459
I'm not mad.

03:30.461 --> 03:32.694
I'm just a little sad.

03:35.097 --> 03:38.867
Luckily, I've got all
weekend by myself to...

03:38.869 --> 03:40.368
to get over it.

03:45.341 --> 03:47.309
Would you like to go fishing this weekend?

03:47.311 --> 03:49.077
You don't want me to go.

03:49.079 --> 03:51.279
Oh, but I do.

03:52.548 --> 03:55.684
It doesn't feel like you do.

03:57.486 --> 03:58.520
Come on, please?

03:58.522 --> 03:59.487
I... it'll be fun.

03:59.489 --> 04:00.455
Well, now you're begging,

04:00.457 --> 04:02.824
so I feel like I have to say yes.

04:04.093 --> 04:05.226
Thank you.

04:05.228 --> 04:07.195
Hey...

04:07.197 --> 04:09.564
you're welcome.

04:13.002 --> 04:15.270
What the hell just happened to me?

04:23.612 --> 04:26.614
What is that odd smell in your RV?

04:26.616 --> 04:28.583
Is it coming from the
bathroom or the fridge?

04:28.585 --> 04:29.784
Fridge.

04:29.786 --> 04:32.320
Oh, then it's urine.

04:33.555 --> 04:34.522
I said "fridge."

04:34.524 --> 04:36.624
And I said "urine."

04:36.626 --> 04:37.725
It's puma urine.

04:37.727 --> 04:38.993
It's a bear repellent.

04:38.995 --> 04:41.028
Yeah. Works on people, too.

04:41.030 --> 04:42.430
Mark my words,

04:42.432 --> 04:44.832
when you see a mama grizzly
circling the campsite,

04:44.834 --> 04:48.803
you'll be splashing it on
like it's English Leather.

04:48.805 --> 04:50.905
You happy? You got your way.

04:50.907 --> 04:53.441
Now our guys' weekend is
turning into a couples' retreat.

04:53.443 --> 04:55.609
Oh, Molly's coming? That's great.

04:55.611 --> 04:58.145
Evens up the teams for Scattergories.

04:58.147 --> 04:59.814
Sure, bring all the board games.

04:59.816 --> 05:01.849
It's not like we're gonna be
able to do anything fun anyway.

05:01.851 --> 05:03.751
(high-pitched voice): "Cigars
will stink up the tent."

05:03.753 --> 05:05.219
"Slingshots are dangerous."

05:05.221 --> 05:07.488
"Cherry bombs are a
terrible way to catch fish."

05:07.490 --> 05:11.258
Boy, we sure blasted
our limit last year, huh?

05:11.260 --> 05:13.093
Yeah, well, now we're gonna
have to rely on our wits.

05:13.095 --> 05:14.295
Did you hear what I said, Carl?

05:14.297 --> 05:15.563
Our wits.

05:15.565 --> 05:18.132
Where can I put these?

05:18.134 --> 05:20.167
I thought you already packed your stuff.

05:20.169 --> 05:22.002
I got some extra baggage.

05:23.371 --> 05:26.006
I hope you boys are ready to become men.

05:26.008 --> 05:27.641
Mama's bringing moonshine.

05:31.379 --> 05:34.048
I did not start this chain of events.

05:34.050 --> 05:36.150
Nor did I have the balls to stop it.

05:38.753 --> 05:41.121
I have always wanted to go
on one of Mike's guy trips,

05:41.123 --> 05:42.656
if only to observe, you know?

05:42.658 --> 05:44.525
What do they talk about? What do they eat?

05:44.527 --> 05:45.592
Do they sleep alone?

05:45.594 --> 05:47.327
Or all together in a pile, like kittens?

05:47.329 --> 05:48.529
Oh...

05:49.631 --> 05:52.299
I hope that's true.

05:52.301 --> 05:54.902
Well, I'm just happy you
and Mom are coming along.

05:54.904 --> 05:56.470
You know, I've been dreading this weekend.

05:56.472 --> 05:58.138
Why?

05:58.140 --> 05:59.373
I don't know.

05:59.375 --> 06:01.041
Carl and I are kind of at a weird place

06:01.043 --> 06:03.110
- in our relationship right now.
- What do you mean?

06:03.112 --> 06:04.611
Like, "where is this going" weird?

06:04.613 --> 06:06.046
Or "don't tell your sister

06:06.048 --> 06:09.549
because it might haunt her dreams" weird?

06:09.551 --> 06:11.051
The first one.

06:11.053 --> 06:12.652
Okay. Good.

06:12.654 --> 06:15.355
'Cause that image of Carl
in nothing but a Zorro mask

06:15.357 --> 06:17.691
still kind of keeps me up at night.

06:19.427 --> 06:22.429
The thing is, I like Carl.

06:22.431 --> 06:24.397
A lot.

06:24.399 --> 06:26.900
He is so kind and attentive

06:26.902 --> 06:30.103
and just crazy about me.

06:30.105 --> 06:33.006
So, what's... what's the problem?

06:33.008 --> 06:36.242
I kind of had a quickie
with my ex-boyfriend.

06:36.244 --> 06:37.210
What do you mean "kind of"?

06:37.212 --> 06:38.545
Kind of definitely.

06:38.547 --> 06:40.613
Kind of... how could you do that?

06:40.615 --> 06:42.048
I don't know, it just happened.

06:42.050 --> 06:44.517
I got a text saying he found my sunglasses.

06:44.519 --> 06:45.752
But it wasn't so much a text

06:45.754 --> 06:48.454
as a picture of my sunglasses on his penis.

06:50.691 --> 06:54.127
And when I went to go get
them, they were still there.

06:54.129 --> 06:56.529
Okay, you said you weren't
gonna haunt my dreams!

06:56.531 --> 06:57.830
- I'm sorry! I'm so sorry...
- No, you're not!

06:57.832 --> 06:59.299
- I don't think you...
- Hey. - Hey.

06:59.301 --> 07:01.901
Hey...

07:01.903 --> 07:03.436
What's going on?

07:03.438 --> 07:04.771
Nothing.

07:04.773 --> 07:07.006
Why would anything be going on?

07:07.008 --> 07:09.075
Well, because I asked
you to pack the cooler.

07:09.077 --> 07:10.743
Yeah, well, all right, here you go.

07:10.745 --> 07:12.945
Take it away.

07:14.148 --> 07:16.749
I know what's happening here.

07:18.452 --> 07:20.419
I knew it. Healthy snacks.

07:20.421 --> 07:22.355
- Where's my beef jerky?
- Ah...

07:22.357 --> 07:24.490
Oh, you got us!

07:24.492 --> 07:26.559
(Victoria and Molly laugh nervously)

07:26.561 --> 07:28.127
What'd I tell you, Carl?

07:28.129 --> 07:29.328
Turn your back for a second,

07:29.330 --> 07:31.030
they start playing Hide the Jerky on you.

07:31.032 --> 07:32.198
Mm-hmm.

07:34.468 --> 07:35.801
You little devil.

07:35.803 --> 07:37.236
What other mischief you been up to?

07:37.238 --> 07:39.338
- Well, to be honest...
- MOLLY: Hey!

07:39.340 --> 07:40.406
What is it... wh...

07:40.408 --> 07:42.041
what is with the third degree, Carl?

07:42.043 --> 07:45.644
Can't you see she that feels
guilty enough about the jerky?

07:45.646 --> 07:47.113
Can't you see that?

07:48.982 --> 07:51.183
This is why they don't invite girls!

