08:10.321 --> 08:12.721
I wonder what changed.

08:12.723 --> 08:14.290
Uh, he's getting a little cranky.

08:14.292 --> 08:16.025
Is there a juice box for him back there?

08:16.027 --> 08:18.027
He's already had two.

08:18.029 --> 08:20.162
Just gimme.

08:22.098 --> 08:23.532
I mean, what would you have done?

08:23.534 --> 08:25.267
They were very expensive sunglasses.

08:25.269 --> 08:27.803
Ugh. I don't want to see that.

08:27.805 --> 08:29.471
See what?

08:29.473 --> 08:31.306
Nothing. Victoria's just...

08:31.308 --> 08:33.375
having some trouble with her cell phone.

08:33.376 --> 08:34.775
Really? Let me take a look at that.

08:34.778 --> 08:36.511
No, no, no. No. Ten and two.

08:36.514 --> 08:38.080
Hands on the wheel.

08:38.082 --> 08:40.515
Besides, it's not really
her phone, it's her plan.

08:40.518 --> 08:41.884
Oh, yeah? What's the problem?

08:41.885 --> 08:45.087
Her old provider is trying
to get her to switch back.

08:45.089 --> 08:46.321
But she's very happy

08:46.323 --> 08:47.589
with her current service. Right?

08:47.591 --> 08:48.824
I am.

08:48.826 --> 08:50.325
But you know how I have trouble

08:50.327 --> 08:52.794
committing to long-term contracts.

08:52.796 --> 08:54.696
You've been hopping from plan to plan

08:54.698 --> 08:57.199
and that's not working out for you, is it?

08:57.201 --> 08:59.468
That's true.

08:59.470 --> 09:01.536
I mean, look at me. I've
been with the same provider

09:01.538 --> 09:03.805
for three years and I am very happy.

09:03.807 --> 09:05.006
What are you talking about?

09:05.008 --> 09:06.408
You complain about 'em all the time.

09:06.410 --> 09:08.677
Well, I still love him.

09:09.712 --> 09:11.646
I'm with Victoria on this.

09:11.648 --> 09:13.582
It's hard to stay loyal
with the other companies

09:13.584 --> 09:15.750
dangling special offers in your face.

09:15.752 --> 09:17.752
I say just pick one.

09:17.754 --> 09:20.722
They're all gonna screw you in the end.

09:20.724 --> 09:22.490
You ever thought about a group plan?

09:22.492 --> 09:24.059
She does not need a group plan.

09:24.061 --> 09:26.261
Just drink your juice.

09:29.732 --> 09:31.032
(Carl scoffs)

09:31.034 --> 09:33.101
I... I can't believe we
pass this place every year

09:33.103 --> 09:34.302
and have never stopped.

09:34.304 --> 09:36.271
You know, what might have kept us away is

09:36.273 --> 09:40.275
that big sign out front
that says "Antiques."

09:40.277 --> 09:42.310
I... I thought it'd be a
little treat for the ladies.

09:42.312 --> 09:43.845
It is.

09:43.847 --> 09:46.481
And thank you very much.

09:46.483 --> 09:47.682
(chuckles)

09:47.684 --> 09:50.919
(whispering): Come here,
come here, come here.

09:52.655 --> 09:54.856
I... I miss you already!

10:00.629 --> 10:02.730
Hey, let me ask you something.

10:02.732 --> 10:04.932
Y... you think Victoria's
been acting differently?

10:04.934 --> 10:06.400
We're all acting differently.

10:06.402 --> 10:09.604
Look where we are, it's not natural.

10:09.606 --> 10:11.873
No, I'm telling you, for,
like, the last week or so,

10:11.875 --> 10:13.374
she's been a little distant, you know?

10:13.376 --> 10:14.709
And it's little things.

10:14.711 --> 10:17.111
Like, the other night, we went
out to eat at a restaurant,

10:17.113 --> 10:18.579
I was wearing my "I'm hers" T-shirt,

10:18.581 --> 10:21.015
she wasn't wearing her "I'm his."

10:21.017 --> 10:24.085
I looked like an idiot.

10:26.955 --> 10:29.690
You are an idiot.

10:31.993 --> 10:34.695
No, man, I... I got to
step my game up, you know?

10:34.697 --> 10:36.297
Be more attentive to her needs, you know?

10:36.299 --> 10:38.399
Truly start listening to her.

10:38.401 --> 10:39.734
Or maybe skip all that work

10:39.736 --> 10:41.936
and just buy her something very expensive.

10:41.938 --> 10:43.637
No, no, no, look, look,
don't get desperate.

10:43.639 --> 10:46.106
Now, you got a good thing going
with Victoria... don't ruin it.

10:46.108 --> 10:47.842
Yeah, but I don't want to lose her, Mike.

10:47.844 --> 10:48.976
You're not gonna lose her.

10:48.978 --> 10:50.811
Look, relationships,
they got ebbs and flows.

10:50.813 --> 10:52.179
Like me and Molly, okay?

10:52.181 --> 10:54.515
Whenever I feel like maybe
she's a little bit sick of me,

10:54.517 --> 10:56.150
I make an effort.

10:56.152 --> 10:58.218
I unload the dishwasher a couple times,

10:58.220 --> 11:00.187
we're right back on track.

11:00.189 --> 11:01.588
All right, I hope you're right.

11:01.590 --> 11:02.556
No, I am right.

11:02.558 --> 11:04.091
And if you do do the dishwasher thing,

11:04.093 --> 11:06.059
make sure they're clean
before you unload it.

11:06.061 --> 11:08.262
It really pisses them off.

11:09.164 --> 11:11.732
My stomach is queasy, I'm hot.

11:11.734 --> 11:14.401
Every time I look at Carl, I feel terrible.

11:14.403 --> 11:15.936
Good, you should, it's called guilt.

11:15.938 --> 11:18.472
Darn it, I thought it
was just food poisoning.

11:18.474 --> 11:20.641
How could you do this to such a great guy?

11:20.643 --> 11:22.576
Carl doesn't deserve this,
he deserves your loyalty

11:22.578 --> 11:24.144
and your love and your honesty.

11:24.146 --> 11:25.646
So you think I should tell him what I did?

11:25.648 --> 11:28.048
No, absolutely not.

11:28.050 --> 11:29.483
But you just said, "Be honest."

11:29.485 --> 11:30.784
Not about this.

11:30.786 --> 11:32.819
That's just gonna make
you feel better, not him.

11:33.821 --> 11:35.422
What, do you want to
break this guy's heart?

11:35.424 --> 11:37.991
Oh, my... of course not.

11:37.993 --> 11:40.193
Are you gonna cheat on him again?

11:40.195 --> 11:43.096
- I hope not.
- Victoria!

11:43.098 --> 11:44.264
I won't.

11:44.266 --> 11:45.765
Okay, then, you take it to the grave.

11:45.767 --> 11:47.267
You bury it, you cover it with lime,

11:47.269 --> 11:48.602
you burn the clothes that you wore,

11:48.604 --> 11:50.203
and you never speak of this again.

11:51.639 --> 11:53.273
What about the sunglasses?

11:53.275 --> 11:56.843
Oh, God, tell me those are not the ones.

11:59.313 --> 12:01.815
I kind of went through
a lot to get them back.

12:10.157 --> 12:14.661
Hey, look, the last guy who
got dragged in here by his wife.

12:14.663 --> 12:16.663
Very funny.

12:16.665 --> 12:20.266
So you gonna tell me
what the hell's going on?

12:20.268 --> 12:21.668
What are you talking about?

12:21.670 --> 12:23.703
You and Victoria... something's fishy.

12:23.705 --> 12:26.005
Well, we are on a fishing trip.

12:26.007 --> 12:27.207
Ha...

12:29.109 --> 12:31.244
You're not fooling anybody.

12:31.246 --> 12:32.378
Even Carl?

12:32.380 --> 12:33.546
So there is something.

12:33.548 --> 12:35.081
I didn't say that, I...

12:35.083 --> 12:37.050
Look, Carl's spinning out enough as it is.

12:37.052 --> 12:38.318
Is there something I need to know?

12:38.320 --> 12:41.687
Mike, some things a...
are better left unsaid.

12:41.689 --> 12:43.856
Okay, well, say it to me, and I'll decide.

12:43.858 --> 12:46.192
Ooh...

12:48.028 --> 12:49.729
Hey! No, hey.

12:51.098 --> 12:52.431
Now, look, I'm your husband.

12:52.433 --> 12:54.300
You can't lie to me.

12:54.302 --> 12:55.901
Well, she's my sister; yes, I can.

12:55.903 --> 12:57.169
Besides, I'm not lying to you,

12:57.171 --> 13:00.172
I'm just not, you know,
telling you the truth.

13:01.475 --> 13:03.509
Did she mess around on him?

13:03.511 --> 13:05.077
Okay, look.

13:05.079 --> 13:07.113
I know you don't want to rat out Victoria.

13:07.115 --> 13:08.681
So you don't have to say anything, okay?

13:08.683 --> 13:11.083
Just blink once for yes,

13:11.085 --> 13:12.618
and twice for no.

13:19.626 --> 13:21.160
You have to blink sometime.

13:21.162 --> 13:23.295
No, I don't.

13:24.297 --> 13:26.198
Did you blink when I blinked?

13:26.200 --> 13:28.133
- I don't know, did I?
- Aah!

13:29.536 --> 13:31.370
Okay. All right, fine.

13:31.372 --> 13:33.973
But we've got all weekend
for those peepers of yours

13:33.975 --> 13:35.374
to tell me what's what.

13:38.612 --> 13:40.779
Oh, yeah.

13:49.122 --> 13:51.323
Oh, God, that feels good.

13:54.394 --> 13:56.094
(clears throat) Hey, uh, Victoria,

13:56.096 --> 13:57.596
while we're waiting for those two,

13:57.598 --> 13:59.531
could you, uh, put that visor down?

13:59.533 --> 14:01.533
I'm getting a glare.

14:01.535 --> 14:03.368
We're parked in the shade.

14:03.370 --> 14:06.071
Catching a little something
off the side mirror.

14:06.073 --> 14:06.972
Well, how's the visor...

14:06.974 --> 14:10.008
Just please put the damn thing down.

14:10.010 --> 14:11.276
(gasps)

14:11.278 --> 14:12.911
Would you look at that?

14:12.913 --> 14:17.315
How did an exquisite $218
turquoise necklace get up there?

14:20.486 --> 14:21.920
Carl, why'd you do this?

14:21.922 --> 14:23.922
I'm just stepping up my game.

14:23.924 --> 14:25.690
You know, perfect jewels
for my perfect jewel.

14:25.692 --> 14:27.025
No, I'm not perfect.

14:27.027 --> 14:28.360
Well, you are to me.

14:28.362 --> 14:31.363
MIKE: All right, let's go.

14:31.365 --> 14:33.865
Carl, you don't know me as
well as you think you do.

14:33.867 --> 14:36.434
Sometimes, I make mistakes, okay?

14:36.436 --> 14:37.669
I'm human.

14:37.671 --> 14:39.371
The most perfect one ever created.

14:39.373 --> 14:41.706
Oh, my God, why are
you being so damn nice?!

14:41.708 --> 14:43.908
Baby, wait!

14:46.145 --> 14:47.879
Don't tell him, please don't tell him.

14:47.881 --> 14:49.013
Don't tell him what?

14:52.685 --> 14:55.220
Damn your crazy eyes.

15:02.128 --> 15:03.294
Hey.

15:03.296 --> 15:04.829
Hey.

15:09.335 --> 15:11.002
I need to apologize.

15:11.004 --> 15:12.637
For what?

15:12.639 --> 15:14.405
You have done nothing wrong.

15:14.407 --> 15:15.907
That's not true.

15:15.909 --> 15:18.743
When it comes to women,
I do everything wrong.

15:18.745 --> 15:21.079
I fall too far, too fast.

15:21.081 --> 15:24.315
I say too much, I spend too much.

15:24.317 --> 15:25.850
I am too much.

15:25.852 --> 15:29.587
Oh, baby, you got nothing on me.

15:29.589 --> 15:32.056
I'm all messed up.

15:32.058 --> 15:35.092
When I find a good guy, I'm bad.

15:35.094 --> 15:38.362
And when I find a bad guy, I'm good.

15:38.364 --> 15:40.765
Yeah, which guy am I?

15:40.767 --> 15:41.699
You're a good one.

15:41.701 --> 15:43.901
Uh-oh.

15:45.037 --> 15:48.039
This is really hard for me to say.

15:48.041 --> 15:49.040
Just say it.

15:49.042 --> 15:51.075
Okay. (Clears throat)

15:51.077 --> 15:52.276
Here it goes.

15:54.212 --> 15:57.381
I don't think we should
sleep with other people.

15:58.450 --> 16:00.885
Y... you mean, be exclusive?

16:00.887 --> 16:02.453
Yes.

16:03.588 --> 16:05.556
Yeah, I thought we were.

16:06.958 --> 16:09.293
Oh, good, now it's official.

16:10.295 --> 16:11.428
Wait.

16:11.430 --> 16:12.563
Why?

16:12.565 --> 16:14.865
Did you... ?

16:14.867 --> 16:17.234
You know what?

16:17.236 --> 16:19.236
Never mind.

16:19.238 --> 16:20.571
I don't want to know.

16:20.573 --> 16:22.072
I don't need to know.

16:27.345 --> 16:29.446
That's why I love you.

16:29.448 --> 16:31.648
You do?

16:33.184 --> 16:35.419
I do.

16:49.841 --> 16:52.076
Boy, so much drama.

16:52.078 --> 16:54.678
Is it always like this
on your fishing trips?

16:54.680 --> 16:57.248
Well, usually it's Harry and Samuel

16:57.250 --> 16:59.316
who end up snuggling in the back seat.

16:59.318 --> 17:02.186
Oh, you really do sleep like kittens.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.387
What?

17:03.389 --> 17:04.387
Never mind.

17:04.390 --> 17:05.689
Just step on it.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.358
The others are probably full
of fish and moonshine by now.

17:08.361 --> 17:11.295
Lucky bastards.

17:11.297 --> 17:13.297
Try it now.

17:13.299 --> 17:16.133
(engine turns, doesn't start)

17:16.135 --> 17:18.135
Poor thing, it sounds like Mother

17:18.137 --> 17:21.204
after her first cigar in the morning.

17:21.207 --> 17:24.141
Hey, chubs, not only is
your RV a piece of crap,

17:24.143 --> 17:28.712
but the apple juice in
your fridge tastes like ass.

17:28.714 --> 17:30.881
Well, you're close.

17:32.951 --> 17:34.384
Bad news... this engine's shot.

17:34.386 --> 17:35.719
Looks like we're not going anywhere.

17:35.721 --> 17:37.554
In the driveway or in the woods...

17:37.556 --> 17:39.890
moonshine tastes the same to me.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.558
You know what?

17:41.560 --> 17:44.628
Maybe we should just take
this party to the backyard.

17:44.630 --> 17:46.697
I'll fill up the kiddie
pool, we'll stick our feet in.

17:46.699 --> 17:48.632
It'll be just like the lake.

17:48.634 --> 17:50.133
Actually, a weekend without Mike and Carl

17:50.135 --> 17:51.768
sounds pretty good to me.

17:51.770 --> 17:53.303
Yeah, let's do this!

17:53.305 --> 17:55.572
Uh, does this mean I have to go home?

17:55.574 --> 17:57.007
Oh, honey.

17:57.009 --> 17:59.276
No, course not.

17:59.278 --> 18:01.178
You can go to a movie or something.

